`docs/` is the project's non-code memory: architectural rationale, a
task-priority queue, and a spec for lint rules not yet built. Nothing
here is executed or imported by the codebase — it's read by contributors
and by other `.ctx`/`intent.md` files that point back here instead of
restating history.

The three files serve distinct, non-overlapping purposes and shouldn't be
merged or cross-copied: DECISIONS.md is the append-only ADR log (why
things are the way they are, including reversed designs — check for
superseding ADRs before treating any entry as current), STATUS.md is the
mutable priority-ranked task table (claims about code that can drift
out of sync, unverified against source), and DYLINT_RULES.md is a spec
for nine not-yet-implemented lint rules, two of which have partial
mechanical equivalents already live in `scripts/` (rationale line-count
check, circular-dependency check via cargo-modules) that must stay in
sync until the real dylint rules supersede them.

Editors should treat DECISIONS.md as the authoritative source of "why,"
never restate rationale elsewhere in docs/, and should verify STATUS.md
row claims against actual source before acting on them rather than
trusting line numbers as current.

No intent.md exists for this directory to check against.